quran[14]{c,v,t,f}:
  89,28,""
  89,29,""
  89,30,""
  92,16,"Who denies and turns away."
  92,17,"And Al-Muttaqûn (the pious - See V.2:2) will be far removed from it (Hell)."
  92,18,"He who spends his wealth for increase in self-purification,"
  95,7,"Then what (or who) causes you (O disbelievers) to deny the Recompense (i.e. the Day of Resurrection)?"
  95,8,"Is not Allâh the Best of judges?"
  96,4,"Who has taught (the writing) by the pen."
  96,5,"He has taught man that which he knew not."
  96,6,"Nay! Verily, man does transgress (in disbelief and evil deed)."
  97,1,"Verily, We have sent it (this Qur’ân) down in the night of Al-Qadr (Decree).{1}",footnotes:1:{97:1} "Therein (that night) is decreed every matter of ordainments." [The Qur’ân, (Verse 44:4)]**
  97,2,"And what will make you know what the night of Al-Qadr (Decree) is?"
  97,3,"The night of Al-Qadr (Decree) is better than a thousand months (i.e. worshipping Allâh in that night is better than worshipping Him a thousand months, i.e. 83 years and 4 months)."